str2: Not, lest. A primary particle of qualified negation; not, lest; also (whereas ou expects an affirmative one) whether.

parse: Verb - Present Imperative Active - 2nd Person Plural
str2: To defraud, deprive of, despoil; mid: I endure deprivation; pass: To be bereft of. From apo and stereo; to despoil.

parse: Personal / Reciprocal Pronoun - Accusative Masculine Plural
str2: One another, each other. Genitive plural from allos reduplicated; one another.
If. A primary particle of conditionality; if, whether, that, etc.
From out, out from among, from, suggesting from the interior outwards. A primary preposition denoting origin, from, out.
Harmonious, agreeing with. From sun and phone; sounding together, i.e. accordant.
To, towards, with. A strengthened form of pro; a preposition of direction; forward to, i.e. Toward.
Fitting season, season, opportunity, occasion, time. Of uncertain affinity; an occasion, i.e. Set or proper time.
In order that, so that. Probably from the same as the former part of heautou; in order that.

parse: Verb - Aorist Subjunctive Active - 2nd Person Plural
str2: From schole; to take a holiday, i.e. Be at leisure for; figuratively, to be vacant.
From proseuchomai; prayer; by implication, an oratory.
And, even, also, namely.

parse: Verb - Present Subjunctive Active - 2nd Person Plural
str2: I am, exist. The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist.
On, to, against, on the basis of, at.
Probably from the same as pale; anew, i.e. back, once more, or furthermore or on the other hand.
In order that, so that. Probably from the same as the former part of heautou; in order that.
An adversary, Satan. Of Chaldee origin corresponding to ma'bad; the accuser, i.e. The devil.

parse: Verb - Present Subjunctive Active - 3rd Person Singular
str2: To try, tempt, test. From peira; to test, i.e. Endeavor, scrutinize, entice, discipline.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Accusative 2nd Person Plural
str2: You. The person pronoun of the second person singular; thou.
A primary preposition denoting the channel of an act; through.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Genitive 2nd Person Plural
str2: You. The person pronoun of the second person singular; thou.
Incontinence, intemperance (in wide sense), lack of restraint. From akrates; want of self-restraint.
